Title:     SONET: AT&T intros first high-speed nationwide SONET service.
             (introduces first inter-LATA Synchronous Optical Network
             service called ACCUNET T155) (Local Access and Transport
             Area)


-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Full Text:

The first inter-LATA Synchronous Optical Network (SONET) service will be
available nationwide in more than 200 locations, AT&T announced Monday.

Following a successful trial with Comdisco Disaster Recovery Services,
AT&T is adding a SONET service called ACCUNET T155 to its ACCUNET family
of data communications services. The T155 service offers the highest
network speeds available today over the most reliable network
infrastructure in the industry.

T155 operates at the standard SONET OC-3 rate of 155 megabits per second
(mbps) and is supported by the unsurpassed service restoration capability
of AT&T's FASTAR system. In the event of a service disruption due to a
cable cut or natural disaster, FASTAR (Fast Automatic Restoration) can
find alternate routes and in most cases restore service over a new path
within minutes.

"Sophisticated data applications are accelerating the need for additional
bandwidth," said Robert Aquilina, marketing vice president for ACCUNET
Data Communications Services. "This trial demonstrates that SONET is
ready today to handle customers' long

distance high-speed applications.   Further, it brings us one step

closer to establishing the data superhighway of tomorrow."

The AT&T and Comdisco trial tested the end-to-end interoperability and
capabilities of SONET equipment and service using a variety of disaster
recovery applications. The trial was conducted between Comdisco
facilities in Wood Dale, Illinois and Carlstadt, New Jersey. Ameritech
and New Jersey Bell provided local access links while AT&T provided the
ACCUNET T155 Service for the inter-state connection.

"The trial went flawlessly," said John Sandberg, vice president
networking products and services for Comdisco Disaster Recovery Services.
"We are testing applications that will provide our customers with new
services and capabilities and help them maintain a competitive edge.
ACCUNET T155 gives us the speed and the reliability necessary to achieve
that goal."

The trial utilized a variety of equipment from multiple vendors including
ATM switches, DS-3 multiplexers and channel extension devices.

Medical imaging, super computer communications, and high definition TV
are some of the emerging applications that will use high-speed SONET
transmission capability. At 155 mbps, a medical X-ray can be sent across
the country in under a tenth of a second.

In addition, ACCUNET T155 can be used to combine data applications from
multiple local and wide area networks over a single line, giving
customers greater economies of scale than are now available.

The service will be available under tariff upon customer request. The
price of the service is based on the city-to-city path that the customer
purchases. Flexible term and volume discounts will

be available.   Generally, T155 prices will be 10 to 15 percent

below the price for equivalent bandwidth provided through ACCUNET T45
Service.

AT&T will use the ACCUNET Customer Service Centers to manage and maintain
the T155 service. Expert technicians, who are familiar with the
customer's network, monitor the service 24 hours a day, seven days a
week.

In addition, the AT&T Service Assurance Warranty will apply to ACCUNET
T155. The warranty offers customers credits on the monthly cost of their
service for any outage of a minute or longer in length. Credits for a
single outage can be up to 50 percent of the service cost.
