Title:     America gets wired.
             (plans for National Information Infrastructure) (News
             Monitor) (Brief Article)
Author:    Ross, Randy


-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Full Text:

The administration's plans for a data superhighway are emerging in the
form of several pieces of legislation and a National Information
Infrastructure (NII) blueprint and task force. Developed by Vice
President Al Gore, the longtime patron saint of the Internet computer
network, the NII blueprint drew fire for favoring commercial interests.
In response, a task force was convened to plan a data superhighway that
will benefit the public interest and create jobs.

In Congress, a number of bills aim to develop aspects of the "information
society." The House recently passed and sent to the Senate the National
Information Infrastructure Act of 1993, which promotes remote teaching,
library access, health care, and online government access. The Senate is
considering a similar bill of its own-the National Competitiveness Act of
1993. Other bills seek to promote competition in telecommunications and
provide access to government databases.
